'''John Evan Davies''' (1850 - 1929) was a Welsh Calvinistic Methodist minister. As a boy he attended [[Llandilo]] Grammar School. He later studied at [[Trevecka]] Calvinistic Methodist College, and in [[Glasgow]], graduating in 1880. He held an initial appointment in [[Llanelly]], and further appointments in Jewin, London (1886-1911), and [[Llandilo]] and [[Llanelly]]. He died in Gowerton in 1929.
His written works include a number of articles for 'Y Geninen', a memorial volume to James Hughes (1779-1844) (published 1911), and a volume of poems, 'Blodau'r Grug' (published 1921). <ref>{{cite web|title=John Evan Davies|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-DAVI-EVA-1850.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|last=Williams|first=Griffith John|accessdate= 12 July 2017}}</ref>
