'''Lorraine Code''' {{post-nominals|FRSC}} (born 1937) is Professor Emerita of Philosophy at [[York University]] in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada and a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]]. Her principal area of research is [[feminist epistemology]] and the politics of knowledge.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lorrainecode.com/ |title=Lorraine Code |publisher=Lorraine Code |date= |accessdate=2013-01-14}}</ref>
==Publications== *''Ecological Thinking: The Politics of Epistemic Location''. Oxford University Press, 2006.<ref name=Clough>{{cite web|last=Clough|first=Sharyn Clough|title=Ecological Thinking: The Politics of Epistemic Location|url=http://ndpr.nd.edu/news/25208-ecological-thinking-the-politics-of-epistemic-location/|publisher=University of Notre Dame|accessdate=15 January 2013}}</ref> *''Rhetorical Spaces: Essays on (Gendered) Locations''. Routledge, 1995. *''What Can She Know? Feminist Theory and the Construction of Knowledge''. Cornell University Press, 1991. * ''Epistemic Responsibility.'' Brown University Press, 1987.
